				\begin{document} $$  CP_{i, j}=\begin{cases} \ P_{i, j} \quad \ \text{if} \ | i-j | \geq 4 \ and \ d_{i, j} \leq 7 \text{\AA},\\ \ 0 \quad \ \text{otherwise}, \end{cases}  $$ \end{document}CPi,j=Pi,jif|i−j|≥4anddi,j≤7Å,0otherwise,

where P
i,j is the contact potential of pair (i, j) collected from the work of Keskin et al. [46]; d
i,j is the distance between residue i and j. Note that the neighbors of a target residue are defined as a sphere of a certain radius of 7.0Å [47] based on the side chain center of mass. The overall contact potential of residue i (P
P
i) is calculated as follows: 
