In this algorithm, the number of iterations is initialized as M; L(y,Θ(x)) is the log loss function; y represents the label and Θ(χ) is a decision function; N is the number of residues in RBP170. The GTB algorithm iteratively repeats steps 2-7 to build m different classification trees h(χ,α
